2 (a) In this section, “Program” means the Child Care Scholarship Program.
3 (b) The Department shall administer the Program in accordance with federal law.
4 (c) (1) The Department shall [establish]:
5 (I) ESTABLISH a process that meets the requirements of this
6 subsection for granting presumptive eligibility for a subsidy under the Program; AND
7 (II) INCORPORATE THE FRAMEWORK OF THE YOUTH
8 TRANSITIONING FROM FOSTER PLACEMENT TO SUCCESSFUL ADULTHOOD PILOT
9 PROGRAM AS ESTABLISHED UNDER § 9.5–113.2 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
10 (d) The Department shall award a scholarship under the Program in an amount
11 sufficient to ensure that an individual will not be required to pay a copay for child care if
12 the individual provides proof, as determined by the Department, of:
13 (1) (I) Participation in one of the following programs:
14 [(i)] 1. Federal Special Supplemental Food Program for Women,
15 Infants, and Children;
16 [(ii)] 2. Federal Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program;
17 [(iii)] 3. Federal Housing Act Housing Choice Voucher Program;
18 [(iv)] 4. Supplemental Security Income benefits; or
19 [(v)] 5. Temporary cash assistance; and
20 [(2)] (II) Employment or enrollment in an education or career training
21 program; OR
22 (2) PARTICIPATION IN THE YOUTH TRANSITIONING FROM FOSTER
23 PLACEMENT TO SUCCESSFUL ADULTHOOD PILOT PROGRAM ESTABLISHED UNDER
24 § 9.5–113.2 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
25 9.5–113.2.
26 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
27 INDICATED.
28 (2) “FOSTER YOUTH” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL WHO:

