1 (I) IS AT LEAST 16 YEARS OLD AND UNDER THE AGE OF 22
2 YEARS; AND
3 (II) 1. IS IN OUT–OF–HOME CARE UNDER THE
4 RESPONSIBILITY OF THE STATE; OR
5 2. WAS IN OUT–OF–HOME CARE UNDER THE
6 RESPONSIBILITY OF THE STATE ON THE INDIVIDUAL’S 18TH BIRTHDAY.
7 (3) “PILOT PROGRAM” MEANS THE YOUTH TRANSITIONING FROM
8 FOSTER PLACEMENT TO SUCCESSFUL ADULTHOOD PILOT PROGRAM.
9 (B) (1) THERE IS A YOUTH TRANSITIONING FROM FOSTER PLACEMENT
10 TO SUCCESSFUL ADULTHOOD PILOT PROGRAM IN THE DEPARTMENT.
11 (2) THE PURPOSE OF THE PILOT PROGRAM IS TO ASSIST FOSTER
12 YOUTH IN APPLYING FOR AND ACCESSING SUBSIDIES IN THE CHILD CARE
13 SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM.
14 (C) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADMINISTER THE PILOT PROGRAM.
15 (2) THE PILOT PROGRAM SHALL BEGIN ON OR BEFORE JANUARY 1,
16 2026, AND SHALL END ON DECEMBER 31, 2028.
17 (D) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL REMOVE BARRIERS IN THE CHILD CARE
18 SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM APPLICATION PROCESS FOR FOSTER YOUTH IN THE PILOT
19 PROGRAM BY REMOVING THE FOLLOWING REQUIREMENTS:
20 (1) PROOF OF A FOSTER YOUTH’S EMPLOYMENT OR ENROLLMENT IN
21 AN EDUCATION OR CAREER TRAINING PROGRAM;
22 (2) THE NAME OF THE OTHER PARENT OF THE FOSTER YOUTH’S
23 CHILD; AND
24 (3) A WRITTEN AUTHORIZATION FROM A PARENT IF THE PARENT IS
25 NOT RESIDING IN THE SAME HOUSEHOLD AS THE CHILD.
26 (E) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL TRACK EXPENDITURES ON
27 SCHOLARSHIPS PROVIDED UNDER THE PILOT PROGRAM ON A MONTHLY BASIS,
28 INCLUDING:

4 SENATE BILL 687
1 (I) THE AVERAGE NUMBER OF FOSTER YOUTH RECEIVING
2 SUBSIDIES UNDER THE PILOT PROGRAM; AND
3 (II) THE AVERAGE SCHOLARSHIP AMOUNT RECEIVED BY
4 FOSTER YOUTH UNDER THE PILOT PROGRAM.
5 (2) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 1 OF EACH YEAR OF THE PILOT
6 PROGRAM, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL REPORT TO THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY, IN
7 ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, REGARDING:
8 (I) THE STATUS OF THE PILOT PROGRAM; AND
9 (II) AN EVALUATION IN MEETING THE PILOT PROGRAM’S
10 GOALS TO REMOVE BARRIERS FOR FOSTER YOUTH IN ACCESSING SCHOLARSHIPS.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
